cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NE

The paper presents a method for selecting a small set of time-series features that exhibit strong classification performance and are minimally redundant. This is relevant to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI) as well as data science (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). The method involves dimensionality reduction, which is also relevant to neural networks (cs.NE).
